Privacy Policy

Salvation Army Shona Songbook we respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our mobile application.

1. Information We Collect
This app does not collect, store, or share any personal information. However, it may request permissions for certain functionalities:

Storage Access (if required) – To save favorite hymns locally on your device.
Internet Access – For app updates and improvements (if applicable).
2. How We Use Your Information
Since we do not collect personal data, we only use permissions for the app’s core functionality, such as:

Allowing you to save and access favorite hymns.
Enabling the search feature for hymns.
Providing access to Salvation Army doctrines, history, and prayers.
3. Copyright Disclaimer
We do not own the copyrights to the hymns provided in this app. All hymns and lyrics remain the property of their respective copyright holders. This app is intended for personal and devotional use only and is not for commercial purposes. If you are a copyright owner and believe your content has been used improperly, please contact us, and we will address any concerns.

4. Third-Party Services
This app does not integrate with third-party services or analytics providers that track your data.

5. Data Security
Your data remains on your device, and we do not collect or store any user information on external servers.

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this policy occasionally. Any changes will be reflected in the app or notified to users.

7. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or copyright concerns, please contact us at
:'kazienmachinedeveloper@gmail.com'

By using this app, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
